passage_text: Miralago Subdivision Homes for sale in Ahwatukee Foothills. Miralago at the Foothills is a gated subdivision in the Foothills in Ahwatukee. Miralago is located in the south eastern area of Chandler Blvd and Desert Foothills Parkway. Homes in this gated subdivision were built between 1990 and 1995. A total of 104 houses are in the Miralago subdivision, with 47 of them being single story and the other 57 being 2 story houses.

MiraLago At A Glance: MiraLago is a newer West Parkland gated community of luxury estate homes from 2,100 to over 4,600 square feet under living areas. There are multiple builder models to choose from with elegant 1 and 2-story homes including 3-6 bedrooms, 2- or 3-car garages, and inviting covered entries and patios.

The Miralago is a modern hotel with gardens and outdoor pool set on the shores of Lake Piediluco. It offers comfortable rooms with lake views, LCD TV with satellite channels, parquet floors, and air conditioning. You will enjoy beautiful views of the lake from Hotel Miralago's summer terrace and from the restaurant. The hotel provides free Wi-Fi in the lobby, and it has a TV lounge. A breakfast buffet is served daily.

Parkland to consider its first charter school. Re-posting a story from the Sun-Sentinel. By Lisa Huriash. Parkand, a city whose A-rated public schools lure families to move there, may be getting its first charter school. Somerset Academy, which operates more than 60 schools in Florida, Texas, Nevada and Washington, D.C., is proposing a two-story school of nearly 98,000 square feet for grades kindergarten through eighth. The school, possibly called Somerset Parkland Academy, would open at the northwest corner of University Drive and Hillsboro Boulevard. Plans call for a gymnasium with views of a lake and landscaping that is âlush in nature.â It would be near the Parkland Golf & Country Club, MiraLago and Town Parc communities. Peak enrollment is expected at 1,280.
